cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of base station antenna heights on network performance in dense cellular networks. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the area spectral efficiency (ASE) of ultra-dense small cell networks (SCNs), which is related to information theory. 

3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may discuss the impact of base station antenna heights on multimedia applications in dense cellular networks. 

4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may discuss the control and management of dense cellular networks with varying base station antenna heights. 

5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper may discuss the revolutionized approach of base station architecture and deployment, which may fall under the scope of hardware architecture.
